<!-- Game Description Table -->

<table class="tablestyle" id="table14" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td class="sectional">

<!-- Game Description Header -->
		
		<table class="headertable" id="table15" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
			<tr>
				<td class="headercell">
				<img border="0" src="../../../images/headers/gamedes.jpg" width="240" height="33"></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>Mutants and Street Fighter characters have teamed up to find the missing among their ranks. While they are supposed to be working together, hunting down their arch-enemies Magneto and General Bison, they can't stop fighting one another long enough to begin their mission.
			<br><br>X-Men vs. Street Fighter brings together the incredibly popular team of Marvel mutant super heroes and Capcom's favorite street-fighting team in this home version of the arcade hit. Cyclops, Wolverine and the other members of the X-Men use their mutant powers to fight each other and Ryu, Ken and the gang from the Street Fighter universe, who also fight amongst themselves. Like most fighting games, this one features a multitude of special moves, combos and the like. When starting the game you must choose two characters from either team, one primary and one secondary. The primary character is your fighter, and the secondary character shows up only when you use the Hyper Special Combo. In the arcade version, both of your characters are fighters and they work in tandem like tag-team wrestlers
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>ONLY ONE FIGHTING GAME IS BIG ENOUGH TO HOLD THEM BOTH!
                  <br><br>X-Men vs. Street Fighter pits Marvel's mutants against Capcom's legendary fighters in a slugfest of epic proportions. Now the translation of the #1 arcade blockbuster tears into the PlayStation game console allowing you to perform outrageous moves and link together amazing Chain Combos. X-Men vs. Street Fighter...the collision of two explosive universes in the world's most amazing fantasy fighter.
                  <br>- The home version of the #1 arcade blockbuster
                  <br>- Play as your favorite character form Marvel's mutant heroes or Capcom's famous video game champions
                  <br>- Link super moves to create massive super combos attacks
                  <br>- 20 points towards the Fighter Edge Program
                  <br>- For 1 or 2 players
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>Third person perspective.</li>
			<li>2D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>Comic & Fighting themes.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

